The curia, 116 means, can exist without a princeps, in so far as it is a spiritual unity ; but he forgets to add that the court which he would fain see established in Italy would still be simply the curia reyis Alamaniae. The Papacy at Avignon was in exile, and super flumina Babylonis was its proper lament‚ but the imperial curia was nothing more than a foreign institution, to be imported at Italy’s expense, and no effort of Dante's genius could convert a German invasion into an exile's return.
